,Recommended,407690,23994413,"Posted: 1 July, 2016",all,Cleveland Rock,"This game keeps it simple and doesn't waste your time. When a batter strikes out, it gets right to the next one without making you watch him walk up to the plate. When a play is finished, there are no slow motion replays or commentary to slow down the action. You can wrap up a nine-inning game in no time and move right on to the next one, which makes playing an entire season seem like an actual possibility.It sticks to the basics. There's a roaring crowd, cheerful organ music, and umpires to tell you who's safe and who's out. Despite its simplicity, it also features all the real-life teams, players, and stadiums, keeping you updated with all the latest roster updates.The controls are nice and simple. They remind me of the old days of playing on the SNES as a kid. The pitching and batting are two-dimensional, so the ball never goes above or below the strike zone. The options let you manually control the fielders or give you AI assistance. You can also specify your favorite team, so you can spend less time in the menus and more time playing ball.It's a simple baseball game the way it should be. Just like Mom used to make (if your mom used to make video games)."
